Class SessionEntryListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.session.hazelcast.SessionEntryListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.hazelcast.map.listener.EntryAddedListener<java.lang.String,ExpiringSession>, com.hazelcast.map.listener.EntryEvictedListener<java.lang.String,ExpiringSession>, com.hazelcast.map.listener.EntryRemovedListener<java.lang.String,ExpiringSession>, com.hazelcast.map.listener.MapListener, java.util.EventListener
    Deprecated. 
    Use HazelcastSessionRepository instead.

    @Deprecated
public class SessionEntryListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.hazelcast.map.listener.EntryAddedListener<java.lang.String,ExpiringSession>, com.hazelcast.map.listener.EntryEvictedListener<java.lang.String,ExpiringSession>, com.hazelcast.map.listener.EntryRemovedListener<java.lang.String,ExpiringSession>
    Listen for events on the Hazelcast-backed SessionRepository and translate those events into the corresponding Spring Session events. Publish the Spring Session events with the given ApplicationEventPublisher.
    • entryAdded - SessionCreatedEvent
    • entryEvicted - SessionExpiredEvent
    • entryRemoved - SessionDeletedEvent
    Since:
    1.1
    Author:
    Tommy Ludwig, Mark Anderson
